description:
&lt;p&gt;The Health Services for the Elderly located on the Barnet site are expanding and we are opening two new specialist HSEP wards. This is an exciting opportunity to develop and build new teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As acute medical wards, we look after a variety of different medical conditions, including palliative care, oncology, tissue viability, endocrinology, renal, cardiology, gastroenterology and delirium, dementia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dedicated, experienced or newly qualified registered nurses to join our passionate, committed and innovative team that deliver excellent standards of care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What can we offer you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want you to be the best you can be and promise to support you in achieving your goals through our in-house training programs and tertiary study at our affiliated universities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Training and support is provided whilst we develop your existing skills and knowledge in each aspect of the acute elderly care environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Personal and professional growth is encouraged through work based learning programs. These programs cover a broad range of clinical and non-clinical skills that aid you in building your professional portfolio in advanced nursing, leadership, research and more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Academy aims to develop a team of practitioners, with knowledge and skills to care for patients within HSEP wards and also including rotational posts if you are interested in gaining other skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Matron Anna Smolec - anna.smolec@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Matron Anna Smolec - anna.smolec@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
